criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Subject inclusion criteria were:

          -  all of the subjects have to have auditory thresholds lower than 20 dB HL at all of the
             frequencies evaluated (octave frequencies between 0.25 to 8 kHz), bilaterally;

          -  type A tympanometric curves with presented ipsilateral and contralateral acoustic
             reflexes;

          -  95% or higher correct responses for each ear in the dichotic digit test.

        Subject inclusion criteria also included negative histories for audiologic, otologic, head
        trauma, and neurologic involvement.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Hearing loss;

          -  Auditory processing disorder;

          -  Histories of audiologic, otologic, head trauma, and neurologic involvement.
